  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Stenting is an alternative to traditional surgery in the treatment of carotid stenosis.The
      intra and/or postprocedural cerebral embolization remains the most frequent complication.

      The type of carotid stent and of cerebral protection are the two most important variables
      potentially affecting the rate of cerebral microembolization. So far there no consensus on
      the the best stent and cerebral protection.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
