  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

        significant, unilateral carotid artery stenosis with soft plaque defined as:

          -  symptomatic patients: &gt; 1.3 m/sec peak systolic velocity and &gt; 50% diameter stenosis
             by Doppler ultrasound and &lt; 60 hounsfield unit by CT angiography

          -  asymptomatic patients &gt; 2.5 m/sec peak systolic velocity and &gt; 70% diameter stenosis
             by Doppler ultrasound and &lt; 60 hounsfield unit by CT angiography

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  severe cerebral vasculopathy with cognitive impairment

          -  contraindication to double antiplatelet treatment

          -  controlateral carotid occlusion
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
